Subsequently, the sensitivity of CMCS@N, S-CDs/Rh6G for SY detection was explored by three parallel measurements. As depicted in Fig. 4
                        A–as the SY concentration raised from 0.26 μM to 100 μM, the intensity of the ratiometric fluorescence nanosphere probe gradually decreased. Specifically, a strong linear relationship was obtained between the F1/F2 ratio (where F1 and F2 represented the peak areas of N, S-CDs and Rh6G, respectively) and SY concentrations (Fig. 4B). Within the range of 0.26 μM–100 μM, the liner equation was F1/F2 = 0.05368[SY] + 8.3768 (R2 = 0.9993), with a SY detection limit (LOD, S/N = 3) of 0.078 μM. Additionally, our CMCS@N, S-CDs/Rh6G exhibited a broader linear range and lower LOD for SY compared to previous studies (Table 1
                        ).
